  "commentary": "With SPX at 6586.55 trading below the GEX flip at 6595, dealers are positioned to provide upside support through delta hedging flows as their long gamma position requires buying dips. The massive positive gamma wall at 6600 (75.5B) creates a strong magnetic effect that should cap upside momentum, while the 6570 negative gamma floor (-11.8B) provides downside buying interest. The recent GEX surge reinforces the PIN regime's mean-reverting characteristics, with dealers likely to fade moves away from the 6595-6600 pivot zone.\n\nKey levels: Watch for dealer selling pressure into any rally toward 6600, and expect stabilizing flows if price approaches 6570 support.\n\nBottom line: expect price to get pulled back toward 6595-6600 with limited downside below 6570.",
